{"author":{"id":"cff9ab1d2ee9741039b2a60d90cca378a5320ba753398f6f3df8d03abcebee1b"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1770886169,"nonce":"L4jqJDvhQ5cH+pNJlK9TQ0nj7dw=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDORKr0287qSCEQ","github-url":"https://github.com/bonanzahq/bonanza/issues/46","origin":"github"},"title":"Autocomplete CORS errors when accessing via Caddy proxy","message":"The borrower search autocomplete fails with CORS errors when the app is accessed through Caddy on port 8080.\n\n**Root cause:** The autocomplete source URL is hardcoded to http://localhost:3000 in app/views/borrowers/_search.html.erb:1:\n\n  data: { \"autocomplete-source-value\": \"http://localhost:3000/autocomplete/borrowers/\" }\n\nWhen accessing via Caddy (port 8080) or Tailscale, the browser blocks cross-origin requests to localhost:3000.\n\n**Fix:** Use a relative URL or Rails path helper instead of hardcoding the host and port.\n\n**Affected file:** app/views/borrowers/_search.html.erb:1","files":null}]}